text.0: Indian-Americans were an unusually prominent campaigning target this election, thanks to Kamala Harris' presence on the ballot. But the campaign to win their votes was far removed from the concerns of most American voters. https://t.co/zPhu7YkgAw
text.1: Large parts of the President's base are expecting a Trump landslide tonight, despite the polls. Trump himself has played a big part in fuelling that idea. https://t.co/1cpdVWLcaK
text.2: The United States went into this election underprepared to deal with disinformation threats, according to one of the experts we spoke to. https://t.co/xQkqvbVvJ4
text.3: There might not be a definitive result tonight! Here's why that's ok: https://t.co/dRMQUJ9ABw
text.4: Residents of Flint received robocalls claiming that they should vote tomorrow because of long queues. FBI investigating the calls now. #ElectionDay https://t.co/gLqyAui5jT
text.5: Our Senior Editor @ixisnox spoke to @Siftedeu about the work we’re doing and the challenges posed by misinformation in tonight’s election. https://t.co/MIhqiqw8OK
text.6: This map shows the spread of the hashtag 'stopthesteal' started by lawyer and conservative pundit Will Chamberlain. The hashtag appears to be explicitly anti-Democrat and is focused on seeding the narrative that the Dems are stealing votes in Philadelphia.
text.7: A big account behind the spread of unsubstantiated rumours of voter suppression in PA is @PhillyGOP, apparently the official account of the local Republican Party. https://t.co/iocJ5Mh56b
text.8:
Looking like this is going to be the major disinformation narrative coming out of polling day: unusually long lines in Rep. districts, much less in Dem districts, hence shenanigans.

Remember that we know Dems voted early, Reps didn't, and that COVID measures mean longer lines. https://t.co/BLvPE3WUXx
text.9: In the most baffling strategy going, Q supporters are recommending some of them vote blue to ensure the inevitable Trump landslide doesn't look like cheating. https://t.co/CaX5qN7yIN
text.10: My colleague @multiplebears wrote about the US elections and whether the result of the election will be clear by tonight or not. #USElection2020 https://t.co/7KyhphCZqb
text.11: Throughout the election season we’ve been working with the board of elections of a major battleground state to assist with election monitoring. We're looking closely at trends and incidences of voter suppression, especially through misinformation. Stay tuned.
